quiz:
  title: Check your knowledge
  questions:
  - content: "Which of these roles is not a built-in role within Azure?"
    choices:
    - content: Owner
      isCorrect: false
      explanation: Owner is a built-in role within Azure.
    - content: Contributor
      isCorrect: false
      explanation: Contributor is a built-in role within Azure.
    - content: Full Access Administrator
      isCorrect: true
      explanation: Full Access Administrator is not a built-in role within Azure
    - content: User Access Administrator
      isCorrect: false
      explanation: User Access Administrator is a built-in role within Azure.
  - content: "You wish to assign a user the right to monitor Azure recovery operations, which of the below roles would grant this permission by assigning the least amount of access to the user?"
    choices:
    - content: Site Recovery Reader
      isCorrect: true
      explanation: This role should be assigned to fulfill the given requirement. It grants the user the ability to monitor Site Recovery operations without granting permissions to anything extra. 
    - content: Site Recovery Operator
      isCorrect: false
      explanation: This role would not provide the access needed in this situation.
    - content: Site Recovery Contributor    
      isCorrect: false
      explanation: This role would grant the permission to monitor Site Recovery operations, however, it would also grant more permission than needed to the user to do their job, therefore it is incorrect.